<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1946-06-04T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1946-06-04T00:00:00-05:00" n="503" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d503">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">Marshall Mission Files, Lot 54–D270:
                            Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">General <persName type="from">Marshall</persName> to
                                    <gloss type="to">Executive Headquarters</gloss>, at
                            Peiping</hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Chungking</hi></placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1946-06-04">4 June 1946</date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>822. The Generalissimo has agreed to the immediate establishment of an
                            advance section of Executive Headquarters in Changchun. General Chou
                            En-lai and I had previously recommended this action. Therefore, please
                            proceed at once to carry out this arrangement with the understanding
                            that the special instructions to govern the function of this advanced
                            section will be issued later.</p>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>